{"lemma":"عَوْنِ","slug":"عَوْنِ","root":"ع.#.ن","root_slug":"ع-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n31107"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"help"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"helper"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a surname"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕawn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31107","headword_ar":"عَوْنٌ","root":"Ewn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnapN","text_ar":"مَعُونَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEowunapN","text_ar":"مَعْوُنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably, with analogy, (TA, [in the CK written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEowanapN","text_ar":"مَعْوَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAnapN","text_ar":"مَعَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnN","text_ar":"مَعُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [respecting the second and last of which see what follows,] are simply substs., (Mgh, Msb, K,) and signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid, help,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, * Msb, * K: *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawonN","text_ar":"عَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of those quasi-inf. ns. that govern like the inf. n., i. e. like the verb; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA SaH~a Eawonu AlxaAliqi A@lomaro'a lamo yajido\n                      \n                     \n                        EasiyrAF mina AlA=maAli A_il~aA muyas~araA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the Creator's aiding the man is true, he will not find such as is difficult, of hopes, otherwise than facilitated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (I 'Ak, §"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEomaAlu AlmaSodari","text_ar":"اـِعْمَالُ المَصْدَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or, accord. to AHei, it is an inf. n. [having no verb]: (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnapN","text_ar":"مَعُونَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoEulapN","text_ar":"مَقْعُلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, Msb, TA,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEawonu","text_ar":"العَوْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, TA;) or, as some say, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlapN","text_ar":"فَعُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAEuwnu","text_ar":"المَاعُونُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, Msb, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Einodaka maEuwnapN","text_ar":"مَا عِنْدَكَ مَعُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAnapN","text_ar":"مَعَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawonN","text_ar":"عَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not with thee any aid"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^axolaAniY fulaAnN mino maEaAwinihi","text_ar":"مَا اَخْلَانِى فُلَانٌ مِنْ مَعَاوِنِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one did not make me to be destitute of his aids"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAwinu","text_ar":"مَعَاوِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnapN","text_ar":"مَعُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnN","text_ar":"مَعُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said by Ks to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnapN","text_ar":"مَعُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and he says that it is the only masc. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEulN","text_ar":"مَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makorumN","text_ar":"مَكْرُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) an ex. of it occurs in a verse of Jemeel cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u","text_ar":"اَىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": Fr says that it is pl. [virtually, though not in the language of the grammarians,] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnapN","text_ar":"مَعُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) and that there is no sing. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEulN","text_ar":"مَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [On this point, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olukN","text_ar":"مَاْلُكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkN","text_ar":"اَلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An aid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an aider, a helper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assistant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) to perform, or accomplish, an affair; (S, Msb;) applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and also to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pl. number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a servant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 95:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an armed attendant, a guard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an officer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a king, and of a prefect of the police, and the like:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAniy~u","text_ar":"عَوَانِيُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawon","text_ar":"عَوْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armed attendant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a guard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who accompanies a Sultán, without pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allowance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^r","text_ar":"تار"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaAnN","text_ar":"اَعْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawonN","text_ar":"عَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, S, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawiynN","text_ar":"عَوِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-pl. n., (K,) said by AA to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaAnN","text_ar":"اَعْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Fr says the like. (TA.) The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~anapu jaA='ato maEahaA","text_ar":"السَّنَةُ جَا=ءَتْ مَعَهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaAnuhaA","text_ar":"اَعْوَانُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When drought comes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its aiders"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2204},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the locusts and the flies and diseases come with it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawonN","text_ar":"عَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that aids, helps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assists, one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for instance, [one says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~awomu Eawonu AlEibaAdapi","text_ar":"الصَّوْمُ عَوْنُ العِبَادَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fasting is the aider of religious service"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lth, TA.) ―         -b3-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","K","Msb","TA","Az"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}